No, 2002 Brazilian spec.  It's the 1600 dual port type 1 engine will all
kinds of parts on it that we've never seen in the US.  I think they would be
hard to get.
I think most of the parts would be unique.  I thought it interesting that it
had the immobilizer, that's an anti-theft system that comes on current
water-cooled VWs.  Means the instrument cluster is totally different as well
as ignition switch, means there is an ECU just for the instruments, etc.
